# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).

---

## [1.0.0] - 2025-02-10
### ðŸŽ‰ Initial Release
This is the first stable release of the **Super Mario Bros â€“ Unity Recreation** project.

#### Added
- Complete World 1-1 level recreation
- Player movement (run, jump, skid, gravity tuning)
- Goomba & Koopa enemy implementations
- Breakable blocks, power-ups, coins, question block logic
- Flagpole ending sequence + castle cinematic
- Custom audio system (SFX + music)
- UI display for coins, lives, world/stage
- Scene hierarchy example image
- WebGL and Windows builds (WebGL requires HTTP server)
- Full documentation in README

#### Changed
- Improved README structure and clarity
- Added correct WebGL instructions
- Removed unused Open Graph meta tags

#### Technical
- Added `.gitattributes` to ensure GitHub detects C# as primary language
- Cleaned repo structure and build directories

